## Current behavior
If `showPopup` method returns a Promise or an Observable, navigation doesn't work properly: it fires only after the timer resolves. (The timer here is a substitute for some async logic). If it returns a primitive or does not return at all - navigations fires well.

## Expected behavior
Expect navigation to fire immediately regardless of the type being returned.

## Minimal reproduction of the problem with instructions
An excerpt from my popup service:
```
showPopup() {
    this.router.navigate([{ // <--------------------- navigation doesn't fire as expected
        outlets: { popup: ['popup'] },
    }]);

    return new Promise((resolve) => {
        setTimeout(() => {
            resolve();
        }, 2000);
    });
}
```

